   <h2>Tate Gallery (<a class="normal" href="http://brea.kfa.st/ak47/004/tate_gallery" title="View Tate Gallery">View</a>)</h2>
  <p><a href="/ak47/004/tate_gallery" title="View Tate Gallery"><img src="/ak47/004/graphics/004_nt.jpg" alt="Tate Gallery" title="Tate Gallery" width="80" height="80" style="float:left; margin-right:5px; margin-bottom:5px;" /></a>I first shot in the Tate Gallery after leaving the Independent Newspaper in 1997, I used it as a closed environment in which to find my own way of seeing again after having worked for somebody else for so long. The initial set of pictures were bought and shown by the Tate Gallery for three years. I have returned to the Tate Gallery on and off ever since mainly because it allows me to enjoy both Art and Photography at the same time. In many ways this project initiated the love of observation and spontaneity that I now practice outside of its walls on the streets of London. The Tate Gallery is a public place and as such allows me to consider this work to be as much Street <br />
Photography as the pictures I make in the rest of the city.</p>

